1 f. A person who is contracting with a permit applicant to perform
2 third-party plan reviews under G.S. 160D-402.1(f)."
3 SECTION 5. G.S. 143-151.12(9) reads as rewritten:
4 "(9) Establish within the Department of Insurance a marketplace pool of qualified
5 Code-enforcement officials available for the following purposes:
6 a. When requested by the Insurance Commissioner, to assist in the
7 discharge of the Commissioner's duty under G.S. 143-139 to
8 supervise, administer, and enforce the North Carolina State Building
9 Code.
10 …
11 c. When requested by a permit applicant under G.S. 160D-402.1(f)."
12 SECTION 6. G.S. 143-151.13 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
13 "(g) A licensed architect or licensed professional engineer who possesses a valid
14 certificate under subsection (f) of this section but is not employed by the State or a local
15 government may utilize that certificate for the limited purpose of performing independent
16 third-party plan reviews under subsections (e) and (f) of G.S. 160D-402.1."
17 SECTION 7. This act becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies to
18 applications submitted on or after that date.
